// Function to rotate an array one position to the right
// Robustness Issue: Does not handle size == 0 gracefully. Accessing arr[size - 1] when size is 0 leads to undefined behavior.
void rotateArrayRight(int arr[], int size) {
    if (size == 0) {
        // This check is added in the driver for safety, but the described flaw is that the function itself doesn't have it.
        // If we want to demonstrate the crash, we'd remove this check.
